rlTBIMib.name: rlTBIMib

revisions.description: Time Range Infrastructure MIBs initial version.

rlTBIMib.description: Time Range Infrastructure MIBs initial version.

rlTBITimeRangeTable.name: rlTBITimeRangeTable
rlTBITimeRangeTable.description: This table specifies Time Based Infra table

rlTBITimeRangeEntry.name: rlTBITimeRangeEntry
rlTBITimeRangeEntry.description: Each entry in this table describes the new time range for ACE. The index is time range name

rlTBITimeRangeAbsoluteStart.name: rlTBITimeRangeAbsoluteStart
rlTBITimeRangeAbsoluteStart.description: Time of start of absolute time range in following format: month day year hh:mm month: 01-12 (January-December) day: 01-31 year: 0-99 (2000-2099) hh: 0-23 (hours) mm: 0-59 (minutes)

rlTBITimeRangeAbsoluteEnd.name: rlTBITimeRangeAbsoluteEnd
rlTBITimeRangeAbsoluteEnd.description: Time of end of absolute time range in following format: month day year hh:mm month: 01-12 (January-December) day: 01-31 year: 0-99 (2000-2099) hh: 0-23 (hours) mm: 0-59 (minutes)

rlTBITimeRangeActiveStatus.name: rlTBITimeRangeActiveStatus
rlTBITimeRangeActiveStatus.description: Shows whether the current time range is active according to the current clock.

rlTBITimeRangeRowStatus.name: rlTBITimeRangeRowStatus
rlTBITimeRangeRowStatus.description: Row Status. It is used for adding/deleting entries of this table.

RlTBIWeekDayList.name: RlTBIWeekDayList
RlTBIWeekDayList.description: Bitmap that includes days of week. Each bit in the bitmap associated with corresponding day of the week.

rlTBIPeriodicTable.name: rlTBIPeriodicTable
rlTBIPeriodicTable.description: This table specifies Time Based Infra Periodic table

rlTBIPeriodicEntry.name: rlTBIPeriodicEntry
rlTBIPeriodicEntry.description: Each entry in this table describes periodic time range.

rlTBIPeriodicTimeRangeName.name: rlTBIPeriodicTimeRangeName
rlTBIPeriodicTimeRangeName.description: Time Range Name the periodic is defined on.

rlTBIPeriodicWeekDayList.name: rlTBIPeriodicWeekDayList
rlTBIPeriodicWeekDayList.description: The bitmap allows to user to select periodic time range for several days at once. The periodic range will be associated with specific days when corresponding bits will be set. If at least one bit has been set in the rlTBIPeriodicWeekDayList, the weekday in rlTBIPeriodicStart and rlTBIPeriodicEnd is not relevant and should be set to zero.

rlTBIPeriodicStart.name: rlTBIPeriodicStart
rlTBIPeriodicStart.description: Time of start of periodic time range in following format: weekday hh:mm weekday: 0-7 (0 means the weekday is not specified, 1-7 are weekdays from Monday to Sunday) hh: 0-23 (hours) mm: 0-59 (minutes) Weekday may be 0 only if periodic time range weekdays were specified in rlTBIPeriodicWeekDayList.

rlTBIPeriodicEnd.name: rlTBIPeriodicEnd
rlTBIPeriodicEnd.description: Time of end of periodic time range in following format: weekday hh:mm weekday: 0-7 (0 means the weekday is not specified, 1-7 are weekdays from Monday to Sunday) hh: 0-23 (hours) mm: 0-59 (minutes) Weekday may be 0 only if periodic time range weekdays were specified in rlTBIPeriodicWeekDayList.

rlTBIPeriodicRowStatus.name: rlTBIPeriodicRowStatus
rlTBIPeriodicRowStatus.description: Row Status. It is used for adding/deleting entries of this table.
